## The Fix

Added `asyncio.Lock()` to make the check-and-decrement operation atomic:

```python
class Inventory:
    def __init__(self):
        self.stock = 10
        self._lock = asyncio.Lock()  # Added lock

    async def purchase(self, user_id, amount):
        async with self._lock:  # Critical section is now atomic
            if self.stock >= amount:
                await asyncio.sleep(0.1)
                self.stock -= amount
                ...
```

**Why it works:** The lock ensures only one coroutine can execute the check-and-decrement at a time. When 5 users try to buy simultaneously, they queue up at the lock. Each one checks *current* stock, decrements if available, then releases the lock for the next user. No more race condition.
